</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AFBEE601637EA" blockId="17.[227,1437,1037,1198]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28508AFBEE64183760" authority="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner, 2022" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,294,1037,1063]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28508AFBEE64183760" box="[227,294,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC285147FBEE64A73760" box="[302,409,1037,1063]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be diagnosed as a genus of haplochromine cichlid within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2854C9FBEE60293760" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[1184,1303,1037,1063]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA87CBE6031EC285168FBCD6733370E" author="Takahashi T." box="[257,525,1070,1097]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" pagination="367 - 382" refId="ref16951" refString="Takahashi T. 2003. Systematics of Tanganyikan cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Perciformes). Ichthyological Research 50: 367 - 382. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 003 - 0181 - 7" type="journal article" year="2003">Takahashi (2003: 379)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28522DFBCD6789370F" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[580,695,1070,1096]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
have “extensively granulated cycloid scales at midbody”, with the “granulations comprising irregularly arranged, variously shaped protrusions over almost entire exposed surface”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2851D5FB9164C137CB" authority="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner, 2022" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" box="[444,511,1138,1164]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC2851D5FB9164C137CB" box="[444,511,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC28526EFB91674D37CB" box="[519,627,1138,1164]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only representative of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28539CFB91615637CB" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[1013,1128,1138,1164]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
with a prognathous lower jaw, versus the retrognathus or isognathus jaw in other genera within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC285455FB70619137EA" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[1084,1199,1171,1197]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="C6BB34F46031EC2854D7FB70602737EA" box="[1214,1305,1171,1197]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="7.[223,293,586,614]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Table 2 continued on next two pages). Images of Lake Tanganyika Tropheni species examined (from Ronco et al. 2021). Images and data were accessed via MorphoSource.org." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" tableUuid="DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32352C46031EC28508AFB3061A6367B" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AFB30645537AA" blockId="17.[227,363,1235,1261]" box="[227,363,1235,1261]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0CEB6236031EC28508AFB30645537AA" bold="true" box="[227,363,1235,1261]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28508AFB30645537AA" bold="true" box="[227,363,1235,1261]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AFAE361A6367B" blockId="17.[227,1436,1280,1340]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">The genus name is derived from the Swahili noun ‛shujaa’, translated into English as ‛brave person’ or ‛warrior’, referring to the notable territorial behaviour of the males of this genus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32352C46031EC28508AFA8067A53448" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AFA80644B363A" blockId="17.[227,373,1379,1405]" box="[227,373,1379,1405]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0CEB6236031EC28508AFA80644B363A" bold="true" box="[227,373,1379,1405]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28508AFA80644B363A" bold="true" box="[227,373,1379,1405]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AFA7067A53448" blockId="17.[226,1438,1426,1808]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
One species in genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC285182FA71674836EB" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[491,630,1426,1452]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horei" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC285182FA71674836EB" box="[491,630,1426,1452]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja horei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC2852E9FA70666136EA" box="[640,863,1426,1453]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Species description, from original German text (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA87CBE6031EC285082FA5564F23696" author="Gunther A." box="[235,460,1462,1489]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" pagination="628 - 632" refId="ref15026" refString="Gunther A. 1894. Descriptions of the reptiles and fishes collected by Mr. E. Coode-Hore on Lake Tanganyika. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1893: 628 - 632." type="journal article" year="1894">Günther 1894: 630</bibRefCitation>
): “Dorsal fin 14 spines 8 rays, L. lat 28, L. trans. 4/9. Teeth bicuspid, cusps subequal, slightly tinged with brown; 28–31 each side of upper jaw outer series. Cheeks naked or few extremely thin scales. In specimen nearly 
<quantity id="4CC1ACAA6031EC28523DFA1E678B3550" box="[596,693,1533,1560]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" unit="in" value="5.0">5 inches</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CC1ACAA6031EC2852ADFA1E660B3550" box="[708,821,1533,1559]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" unit="cm" value="12.7">12.70 cm</quantity>
) long eye diameter nearly equal to depth of soft part of cheek, a little less than width of preorbital and interorbital space, which is flat. Preopercular limbs at right angle. Body height less than length of head, and one third of total (without caudal). Last dorsal spine longest, two fifths of head length. Pectoral fin to, or nearly to, origin of anal fin. Caudal scaleless. Scales rough, some with margins ciliated. Body light greenish, with incomplete brownish cross-bands on upper part of body. Largest specimen cheek and snout with irregular deep brown spots. Soft dorsal and caudal fin with scattered ocelli; milky-white spot between last two anal rays.” In 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2854A9F931607635AB" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1216,1352,1746,1772]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horei" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC2854A9F931607635AB" box="[1216,1352,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja horei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC285526F930645A3457" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
hypertrophied lips absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32352C46031EC2B508AF8D467A731C5" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AF8D464683416" blockId="17.[227,342,1847,1873]" box="[227,342,1847,1873]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0CEB6236031EC28508AF8D464683416" bold="true" box="[227,342,1847,1873]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28508AF8D464683416" bold="true" box="[227,342,1847,1873]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B86014F6031EC28508AF88560A33B49" blockId="17.[226,1437,1894,2063]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28508AF885641834C7" authority="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner, 2022" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,294,1894,1920]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28508AF885641834C7" box="[227,294,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC285159F88464A334C6" box="[304,413,1895,1921]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC285243F88567A334C7" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[554,669,1894,1920]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
tribe of African cichlids, originally defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA87CBE6031EC2854BEF885605C34C6" author="Poll M." box="[1239,1378,1894,1921]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 163" refId="ref15977" refString="Poll M. 1986. Classification des Cichlidae du lac Tanganika. Tribus, genres et especes. Memoires de l'Academie royale de Belgique, Classe des Sciences 45: 1 - 163." type="journal article" year="1986">Poll (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. The diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28511FF86964D734E3" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[374,489,1930,1956]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
is the presence of “extensively granulated cycloid scales at midbody” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA87CBE6031EC28554DF86964653480" author="Takahashi T." pageId="17" pageNumber="40" pagination="367 - 382" refId="ref16951" refString="Takahashi T. 2003. Systematics of Tanganyikan cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Perciformes). Ichthyological Research 50: 367 - 382. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 003 - 0181 - 7" type="journal article" year="2003">Takahashi 2003: 379</bibRefCitation>
). Our observations suggest such granularity of the flank/midbody scales in 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2854DFF84E60173480" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[1206,1321,1965,1991]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC28516BF83264B234AC" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[258,396,2001,2027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horei" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC28516BF83264B234AC" box="[258,396,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Shuja horei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266031EC2851FFF832674A34AC" box="[406,628,2001,2027]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2852E8F83266A634AC" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[641,920,2001,2027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Gnathochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pfefferi">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC2852E8F83266A634AC" box="[641,920,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Gnathochromis pfefferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6031EC2853BCF83261F534AC" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[981,1227,2001,2027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Lobochilotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6031EC2853BCF83261F534AC" box="[981,1227,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Lobochilotes labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at least, but also small ctenii are present. These ctenii are sparse and largely restricted on the margins of this caudal edge of
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B86014F6032EC2B508AFECC67A731C5" blockId="18.[226,1439,303,642]" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">
the scale. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA87CBE6032EC2B513CFECC677A320E" author="Viertler A. &amp; Salzburger W. &amp; Ronco F." box="[341,580,303,329]" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" pagination="541 - 556" refId="ref17244" refString="Viertler A., Salzburger W. &amp; Ronco F. 2021. Comparative scale morphology in the adaptive radiation of cichlid fishes (Perciformes: Cichlidae) from Lake Tanganyika. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society 134: 541 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / biolinnean / blab 099" type="journal article" year="2021">
Viertler 
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B51DCFED364CE320E" box="[437,496,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
report multiple species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B53C8FECC612A320E" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[929,1044,303,329]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
with ctenoid scales on the central flank area. Further detailed work of all described species is needed to determine if the distribution of the granulation and ctenii on midbody scales is diagnostic of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B53AFFE96610332C8" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[966,1085,373,399]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, irrespective of morphological traits, the tribe is unambiguously monophyletic in genome-scale molecular phylogenetic analyses (Ronco 
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B51D9FE5864D33293" box="[432,493,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2021), and endemic to Lake Tanganyika and immediate river systems. Within the tribe, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B513FFE3E64A732B0" authority="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner, 2022" authorityName="Genner &amp; Hsu &amp; Collins &amp; Smith &amp; Saxon &amp; Shechonge &amp; Ngatunga &amp; Turner" authorityYear="2022" box="[342,409,477,503]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Shuja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B513FFE3E64A732B0" box="[342,409,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Shuja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27E60266032EC2B51C9FE3D673232BF" box="[416,524,478,504]" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a monotypic genus and can be distinguished from other representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B517BFDE364BB315D" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[274,389,512,538]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a prognathous jaw (
<figureCitation id="13021DCA6032EC2B5301FDE366E2315C" box="[872,988,512,539]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[227,270,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1391,1213,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-345@18.[227,1436,1213,1815]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 5. Shuja horei gen. et comb. nov.a. Illustration from the original type specimen (Günther 1894).b. A freshly caught specimen collected in 2016 from the Malagarasi River, Ilagala (BMNH 2021.7.15.14). c. Radiographs of the type series (syntypes) from the Natural History Museum (BMNH 1889.1.30.13– 15). Note the prognathous jaw that distinguishes Shuja Genner, Ngatunga &amp; Turner gen. nov. from other genera within the Tropheini Poll, 1986. Radiographs from the Natural History Museum, London (Creative Commons Attribution License (CC BY 4.0)). Scale bars: 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554365/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Fig. 5a–c</figureCitation>
), when all other described species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B5166FDC164BC317B" authorityName="Poll" authorityYear="1986" box="[271,386,546,572]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Tropheini">Tropheini</taxonomicName>
have a retrognathus or isognathus jaw (
<tableCitation id="C6BB34F46032EC2B5309FDC16682317A" box="[864,956,546,573]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="7.[223,293,586,614]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Table 2 continued on next two pages). Images of Lake Tanganyika Tropheni species examined (from Ronco et al. 2021). Images and data were accessed via MorphoSource.org." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" tableUuid="DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE">Table 2</tableCitation>
). These include 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B54EBFDC160AB317A" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1154,1429,546,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Gnathochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pfefferi">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B54EBFDC160AB317A" box="[1154,1429,546,573]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Gnathochromis pfefferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and representatives of 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B519DFDA667A63118" authorityName="Yamaoka, Hori &amp; Kuwamura" authorityYear="1998" box="[500,664,581,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Interochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B519DFDA667A63118" box="[500,664,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Interochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B52C0FDA6667F3118" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1920" box="[681,833,581,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Limnotilapia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B52C0FDA6667F3118" box="[681,833,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Limnotilapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B533BFDA666D43118" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1915" box="[850,1002,581,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Lobochilotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B533BFDA666D43118" box="[850,1002,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Lobochilotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B5392FDA661A73118" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1898" box="[1019,1177,581,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Petrochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B5392FDA661A73118" box="[1019,1177,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Petrochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B54C3FDA660AB3118" authorityName="Nelissen" authorityYear="1977" box="[1194,1429,581,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Pseudosimochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B54C3FDA660AB3118" box="[1194,1429,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Pseudosimochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B508AFD8B644531C5" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1898" box="[227,379,616,642]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Simochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B508AFD8B644531C5" box="[227,379,616,642]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Simochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C397ACC6032EC2B51DDFD8B671E31C5" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1898" box="[436,544,616,642]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Tropheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94DDD5D6032EC2B51DDFD8B671E31C5" box="[436,544,616,642]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="41">Tropheus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="C6BB34F46032EC2B5246FD8B67B431C5" box="[559,650,616,642]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="7.[223,293,586,614]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Table 2 continued on next two pages). Images of Lake Tanganyika Tropheni species examined (from Ronco et al. 2021). Images and data were accessed via MorphoSource.org." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE" pageId="18" pageNumber="41" tableUuid="DF4651C76027EC3E50B6FDA9676331CE">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
